    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-18T14:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-18T14:36:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/8–1850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-18T15:36:00-04:00"
                            >August 18, 1950—3:36 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 18—3:48 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>310. Supplementing our 309, August 18, re developments Rau proposal, <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> has now learned Rau circulated to
                    non-permanent members at meeting this morning copy of draft resolution. No
                    commitments were sought other delegations present or given.</p>
                <p>Shortly after conclusion of meeting Rau advised other conferees by telephone that
                    he had received new instructions from India which would require him reconsider
                    resolutions. Rau did not reveal nature of instructions and it was not clear
                    whether he would redraft his resolution or hold up action on it or any similar
                    one.</p>
                <pb facs="0629" n="609" xml:id="pg_609"/>
                <p>Norwegian delegation requested our views which were outlined to them by Gross
                    basis Deptel 147, August 15.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
